  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How much are businesses using Instagram?",
  "response": "Businesses are increasingly using Instagram as a key platform for marketing, customer engagement, and brand building. Here are some key statistics and trends that highlight its usage:\n\n### 1. **Adoption Rates**\n   - Over **200 million businesses** have an Instagram profile (as of 2023).\n   - **90% of Instagram users** follow at least one business account.\n   - Instagram is one of the most popular platforms for small businesses, with **71% of U.S. small businesses** using it for marketing.\n\n### 2. **Marketing and Advertising**\n   - Instagram is the **second most preferred platform for marketers** (after Facebook).\n   - Over **50% of Instagram users** have discovered new products or services on the platform.\n   - **130 million users** tap on shopping posts monthly, making it a hub for e-commerce.\n\n### 3. **Engagement**\n   - Instagram has **one of the highest engagement rates** compared to other social media platforms.\n   - Brands see an average **engagement rate of 0.83%** on Instagram, higher than Facebook and Twitter.\n   - Stories are a major driver, with **500 million users** interacting with Instagram Stories daily.\n\n### 4. **E-commerce Integration**\n   - Instagram Shopping allows businesses to tag products in posts and stories, making it easier for users to purchase directly.\n   - Over **150 million users** engage with shopping posts each month.\n\n### 5. **Content Strategies**\n   - Businesses are leveraging a mix of **photos, videos, Reels, Stories, and live streams** to connect with their audience.\n   - **Reels** (Instagram's short-form video feature) has seen rapid adoption, with businesses using it to boost visibility and engagement.\n\n### 6. **Demographic Reach**\n   - Instagram is particularly popular among younger audiences, with **71% of users** under 35 years old, making it ideal for targeting Gen Z and Millennials.\n\n### 7. **Paid Advertising**\n   - Instagram ads are used by **over 2 million advertisers**, with the platform generating **$50 billion in ad revenue** in 2022.\n   - Ads on Instagram reach **over 1.28 billion users** monthly.\n\n### 8. **Industry Usage**\n   - Instagram is widely used across industries, including **fashion, beauty, food, travel, and fitness**.\n   - Influencer partnerships are common, with brands collaborating with Instagram influencers to promote products.\n\n### 9. **Global Presence**\n   - Instagram is a global platform, with **India, the United States, and Brazil** being its largest markets.\n\n### Conclusion\nInstagram has become an essential tool for businesses of all sizes, offering a visually driven platform to showcase products, engage with customers, and drive sales. Its continuous innovation (e.g., Reels, Shopping) and high user engagement make it a go-to platform for modern marketing strategies.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
